            <p>Dear Sir&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>The bearer has a little son&#44; whom<lb/> he wishes to be taught how to translate<lb/> Hebrew into English.  I had the boy ad&#45;<lb/>mitted into the Sunday School&#44; and I<lb/> think it might be of some advantage to<lb/> let him to go Mr. Law&#39;s School.  Will you<lb/> please write him a permit&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>Another boy named Abram Cohen<lb/> has been recommended to me by a Christian<lb/> lady.  I visited his father&#39;s family on<lb/> St. Mary Street&#44; and advised that the<lb/> lad should attend Miss Amelia Allen&#39;s<lb/> night school.  You may possibly meet<lb/> him and by allowing him to be entered as<lb/> a pupil&#44; you will oblige<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours truly&#44;<lb/>
                S. Morais.<lb/></p>
            <p>May 11&#44; &#39;91.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
